# Build-context exclusions (audit M508).
#
# The repo-root build context (compose `context: ..`) is shared by every Go service
# plus scraper / stealth-scraper / animepahe-resolver. Their Dockerfiles COPY only
# go.work*, the libs/ and services/ trees, and per-module go.mod/go.sum — never the
# paths below — so excluding these only shrinks the context tarball streamed to the
# Docker daemon on each build; no image content changes. (web, megacloud-extractor
# and vnstat-exporter declare their own narrower contexts and are unaffected.)
#
# DO NOT add libs/, services/, go.work, go.mod or go.sum here — they are required by
# the Go builds.

.git
.gitignore
.github
.claude
.planning
.worktrees
.vscode
.idea

# Frontend has its own build context (../frontend/web); never copied by Go builds.
frontend
**/node_modules

# Docs / planning / markdown — never copied into any image.
docs
**/*.md

# Python caches / venvs (sidecars copy app/ + requirements, not these).
**/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc

# Checked-in host binary (maintenance runs on the host via systemd, not docker).
services/maintenance/maintenance

# Logs / local artifacts
*.log
